<plot>A postmodern romantic comedy. A London university dropout returns to the gritty streets of Hong Kong in search of the childhood memories of her deceased father and for her tax-free inheritance to sustain her Royal-Borough-of-Kensington lifestyle. Unfortunately, she finds out that he died penniless and alone, with only a clue to a treasure he left especially for her. Meanwhile, she runs into her high school tormentor, Charlie, a broke, nervous and lost actor wannabe. Together, they hunt down her father's inheritance to make both their dreams come true. A film about the true value of money and the dull pain of lost identities.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?244743</url></doc>
